Subject: [Caml-list] [ANN] PG'OCaml 2.1

Hallo everyone,

No earth-shattering news for this release.  Version 2.0 (released last 
week)
relied on the List.iteri and List.mapi functions available since OCaml 
4.00.0.
However, it turns out we have users still on OCaml 3.12.1 (or maybe 
older).
This release simply adds those missing functions for compatibility with 
older
OCaml releases.

For more information, please visit the project's homepage:
http://pgocaml.forge.ocamlcore.org/

Also, the new package should be hitting OPAM soon.

Best regards,
Dario Teixeira

